## Analysis Workflow
- SenMayo gene signatures were used to assess senescence-associated transcriptional programs.
- Developmental stage comparisons were performed across PT-Newborn, FT-Newborn, Infant, Child, Adolescent, Young Adult, and PT-BPD groups.
- Gene Ontology enrichment analysis was performed using DAVID and PANTHER annotation databases.
- Statistical summaries and visualization panels were generated using GraphPad Prism.
- Circular heatmaps were generated in R.
- Phenocycler/CODEX spatial imaging data were used for spatial validation of senescence-associated markers.
- Immunofluorescence and spatial marker expression were evaluated for p21, GDF15, ACTA2, Pan-Cytokeratin, and Lamin B1.

